import{_ as e,o,c as t,b as s}from"./app-a6eacc5a.js";const a={},n=s('<h1 id="mouse" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#mouse" aria-hidden="true">#</a> mouse</h1><p>The mouse is an electronic device used for input and <code>navigation</code> on a computer or other digital device. It consists of a small <code>handheld</code> unit with two buttons (left and right) and a <code>pointer</code> that moves across a flat surface, usually a monitor or screen.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p>鼠标是用于在计算机或其他数字设备上输入和导航的电子设备。它由一个带有两个按钮(左和右)的小型手持装置和一个可以在平面上移动的指针组成，通常是显示器或屏幕。</p></details><details class="custom-container details"><summary>words</summary><p>navigation<br><code>英 [ˌnævɪˈɡeɪʃ(ə)n]美 [ˌnævɪˈɡeɪʃ(ə)n]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 导航；航行，航海；航运，水上运输；浏览，访问；领航术，航海术；内河水道（尤指运河）</p></blockquote><p>handheld<br><code>英 [ˈhændheld]美 [ˈhændheld]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 掌上型；手持型</p></blockquote><p>pointer<br><code>英 [ˈpɔɪntə(r)]美 [ˈpɔɪntər]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 指针；指示器；教鞭；暗示</p></blockquote></details><p>The mouse was first <code>introduced</code> in the 1960s by Douglas Engelbart as part of his work at Stanford University. The original &quot;mouse pointer&quot; was designed to allow users to select text on a screen, but it quickly became a popular tool for performing other tasks as well. Today, <code>mice</code> are <code>ubiquitous</code> in both personal and professional computing environments.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p>鼠标最初由道格拉斯·恩格尔巴特于20世纪60年代在斯坦福大学工作时引入。最初的“鼠标指针”被设计成允许用户在屏幕上选择文本，但它很快就成为了执行其他任务的流行工具。今天，鼠标在个人和专业计算环境中无处不在。</p></details><details class="custom-container details"><summary>words</summary><p>introduce ( introducing, introduced, introduces )<br><code>英 [ˌɪntrəˈdjuːs]美 [ˌɪntrəˈduːs]</code></p><blockquote><p>v. 推行；采用；实施；引见</p></blockquote><p>mice<br><code>英 [maɪs]美 [maɪs]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 老鼠（mouse 的复数）<br> n. （Mice）（塞）米采（人名）</p></blockquote><p>ubiquitous<br><code>英 [juːˈbɪkwɪtəs]美 [juːˈbɪkwɪtəs]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 普遍存在的，无所不在的</p></blockquote></details><p>Mice come in many different designs and sizes, and some models offer additional features such as touchpads, scrolling wheels, and multiple buttons. They can connect to computers through USB ports or wirelessly using Bluetooth technology.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p>鼠标有许多不同的设计和大小，有些型号还提供了额外的功能，如触摸板、滚轮和多个按钮。他们可以通过 USB 接口或使用蓝牙技术无线连接到电脑。</p></details><p>In addition to being a <code>convenient</code> tool for navigating and <code>manipulating</code> information on a computer screen, mice have also become symbols of modern computing culture. Many people <code>associate</code> the use of a mouse with the experience of using a computer, and some even consider it an essential component of their daily lives.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p>鼠标不仅是在计算机屏幕上导航和操作信息的方便工具，而且已经成为现代计算机文化的象征。许多人将使用鼠标与使用计算机的经历联系在一起，有些人甚至认为它已经成为了他们日常生活中不可或缺的部分。</p></details><details class="custom-container details"><summary>words</summary><p>convenient<br><code>英 [kənˈviːniənt]美 [kənˈviːniənt]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 方便的，便利的；附近的，方便到达的；&lt;旧&gt;适当的</p></blockquote><p>manipulate ( manipulating, manipulated, manipulates )<br><code>英 [məˈnɪpjuleɪt]美 [məˈnɪpjuleɪt]</code></p><blockquote><p>v. 操纵，摆布；操作，使用；正骨，推拿；篡改；巧妙地移动（某物），巧妙地处理（某事）；校正，转移（储存在计算机上的信息）</p></blockquote><p>associate ( associating, associated, associates )<br><code>英 [əˈsəʊsieɪt]美 [əˈsoʊsieɪt]</code></p><blockquote><p>v. 联想，联系；支持，同意；交往，（尤指）混在一起<br> n. 同事，伙伴；副学士，准学士；副职，副手；准会员；联想<br> adj. 副的，准的，非正式的；联合的，有关连的</p></blockquote></details>',12),c=[n];function i(d,r){return o(),t("div",null,c)}const u=e(a,[["render",i],["__file","30-mouse.html.vue"]]);export{u as default};
